<div style="display: flex; min-height: 800px; width: 900px; justify-content: space-between;">
  <div style="min-width: 400px">
    <h3>Normal</h3>
    {{#power-select options=options selected=selected onchange=(action (mut selected)) as |opt|}}
      {{opt}}
    {{/power-select}}
  </div>
  <div style="min-width: 400px">
    <h3>With vertical collection</h3>
    {{#power-select options=options selected=selected onchange=(action (mut selected))
      optionsComponent="power-select-vertical-collection-options"
      scrollTo=customScrollTo
      as |opt|}}
      {{opt}}
    {{/power-select}}
  </div>
</div>
<ul>
  <li>When the component opens the list must scroll to the selected element. In the vertical-collection the element is not there so it doesn't scroll</li>
  <li>Similar problem when using the arrow keys to navigate options</li>
</ul>